snippet.textDisplay:
The results cant really be argued due to naruto power scaling vs Heroaca power scaling. Age of the manga and story, Guy had a longer running story in a higher scaled world than All Might really could have. I can respect the decision even if Im dissatisfied with it.

The fact that a prime All Might made Guy go quite literally all out, I think itd be more fair to call it a technical draw- atleast in such fashion neither combatant is walking away unaided.

Its for that reason I prefer Heroaca as a series, though- it has a much more "balanced" world in terms of scaling, and while I kinda figured just by the nature of Naruto scaling, All Might wasnt going to win the bout, it wasnt a bad contest.

Madara vs Prime All for One would make an interesting comparison fight though, and depending how you value All for One, there might be an argument for upping what All Might can do here.

Keep in mind, All Might beat All for One down, then got injured (see, Mothers Basement on the All Might v All for One bout) and THEN beat All for One BLIND, basically disabling/crippling the big bad of his story.

No disrespect for Night Guy, but but he never fully incapped Madara.

That said, I agree with having the medic characters of both series giving these 2 a stern lecture not to fight to the death for our amusement, damnit. ^.^

snippet.textDisplay:
Eh, I'm a big fan of All Might but I can understand the reasoning for Guy's victory. Eight Gates is clearly god-level honestly, but BNHA makes All Might seem like a God, so it's tough to pick a favorite. Different universes and different power sets and rules. Obviously in All Might's world he'd be at the top for the most part, but in the Naruto universe it's completely different.


Really if it makes people feel better you could call this a draw, but Guy was "technically" the victor, though Guy will die eventually after using the Eight Gates while All Might will still be alive. You could say All Might won in the long run.
